    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "a failure of strategy? that feels like a pretty harsh way to put it. it's not like i'm not trying to be efficient, i just work with the reality of my local economy. it feels like you're saying if a small shop can't afford a certain wage, then the shop shouldn't exist. shouldn't we also look at the arguments from the other side—like how these laws can actually kill off local competition and leave only the big corporations who can afford the overhead?",
